column5: hey there fellow fishermen and fisherladies has anyone been to gullrock lake lately hows the fishing been hows the water levels
Water levels were down 2-3 foot on August 8-12 while I was there. Fishing was still pretty good. Here is the post others have made.https://www.walleyecentral.com/forums...=184722&page=2
thanks did you fish eyes or pike or both and how did you do we are going up on the 10th -16th

We will be up there same time frame. Said lake level has came up a bit but to heck with it shallow water isnt gunna fear us. Fishing looks to be picking up. We will be at 5 lakes where are you staying.

Hi My group and I were up there last week, best fishing in a long time. It must be the water levels there down from the previous year. The toe of the boot was hot but it was lot's of little fish.with Some good quailty marble eyes mixed in. Larry's kid, first year down and he smashed a 27 inch some quick pics and back she goes. That kid we be smiling for a while.. We were there for a week and that fish was the biggest but we were pulling lot's of 22,23 in a couple of 24. But I like the smaller ones the 16 and 17 for shore lunch. Yumm fish and beans Can't wait for next year
